(Overview) Tj
T*
(Number theory studies the structure and properties of whole numbers.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Learning Objectives) Tj
T*
(- Explain the meaning of Number Theory in Mathematics using accurate subject vocabulary.) Tj
T*
(- Describe the key ideas behind factors, multiples, primes, divisibility, and) Tj
T*
(remainders.) Tj
T*
(- Apply Number Theory to examples such as using prime factorization to find HCF or LCM.) Tj
T*
(- Avoid common errors and build confidence through divisibility tests and factor-based) Tj
T*
(reasoning.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Main Lesson) Tj
T*
(1. Introduction To The Topic) Tj
T*
(Number theory studies the structure and properties of whole numbers. In a textbook) Tj
T*
(lesson, the first goal is to make the mathematical idea clear. Students should be able) Tj
T*
(to explain what Number Theory means, identify where it appears in Mathematics, and) Tj
T*
(describe the main purpose of the topic without relying on memorized sentences.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Core Teaching) Tj
T*
(The central focus in Number Theory is factors, multiples, primes, divisibility, and) Tj
T*
(remainders. This means students must move beyond the overview and understand how the) Tj
T*
(idea actually works. A strong explanation should unpack the rules, relationships, or) Tj
T*
(patterns behind Number Theory and show how those ideas guide correct answers. In) Tj
T*
(Mathematics, success usually depends on understanding the symbols, rules, and steps that) Tj
T*
(belong to the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. How The Idea Is Applied) Tj
T*
(A useful way to teach Number Theory is to connect the explanation directly to using) Tj
T*
(prime factorization to find HCF or LCM. That kind of worked calculation shows students) Tj
T*
(how the topic moves from theory into use. At this stage, the learner should be able to) Tj
T*
(state the relevant rule or principle, explain why it fits the question, and then apply) Tj
T*
(the solution method with confidence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Why Errors Happen) Tj
T*
(One common difficulty in Number Theory is confusing prime numbers with odd numbers or) Tj
T*
(misusing factor rules. This matters because many learners can repeat a definition but) Tj
T*
